Package: endogCopula
Type: Package
Title: Endogeneity Corrections via Gaussian Copulas
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person(given = "Ashwin", family = "Malshe", role = c("aut", "cre"),
    email = "ashwin@malshe.com")
Description: Implements Gaussian copula based estimators for handling
    endogeneity in linear models, including the joint maximum-likelihood
    approach of Park and Gupta (2012) <doi:10.1287/mksc.1120.0718>, the
    two-stage copula generated regressor approach of Yang, Qian, and Xie
    (2025) <doi:10.1177/00222437241296453>, the instrument-free
    nonparametric copula control function approach of Hu, Qian, and Xie
    (2025, National Bureau of Economic Research Working Paper 33607)
    <doi:10.3386/w33607>, the nonlinear-transformation control function
    approach of Breitung, Mayer, and Wied (2024) <doi:10.1093/ectj/utae002>,
    the between-regressor correlation approach of Haschka (2024)
    <doi:10.1093/imaman/dpae018>, and the adjusted estimator of Liengaard,
    Becker, Bennedsen, Heiler, Taylor, and Ringle (2025)
    <doi:10.1007/s11747-024-01055-4>, along with related panel and Bayesian
    formulations. The package provides tools to estimate coefficients,
    obtain bootstrap-based standard errors, and work with residual
    diagnostics across cross-sectional, panel, and Bayesian settings.
